Question: How would you invite your friends to a party if phones and the Internet did not exist?
Answer:
if phones and the internet did not exist, i would either invite my friends by mail or i would go to invite them in person if they lived locally.  the people that i invited by mail would get personalized, handwritten letters from me.  otherwise i could also set a specific time and day of the week and invite people to always come by at that time.